4. old lacunes or lacunar infarcts at the left frontal subcortical white 
matter and centrum semiovale. 
5. focal stenosis at the cavernous segment of right internal carotid 
artery (ICA) and A1 segment of left anterior cerebral artery (ACA); 
segmental stenosis at the P3-4 segment of right posterior cerebral artery 
(PCA). 
6. no evidence of dural sinus thrombosis.
7. bil. maxillary sinusitis. 

Impression :
acute ischemic infarct, right posterior putamen and corona radiata. 
mild cortical brain atrophy with ventriculomegaly and leukoaraiosis. 
old lacunes or lacunar infarcts, left frontal subcortical white matter and 
centrum semiovale. 
focal stenosis, cavernous segment of right ICA and A1 segment of left ACA; 
segmental stenosis, P3-4 segment of right PCA. 
bil. maxillary sinusitis.

ventricles.
3. ventriculomegaly with enlargement and upward displacement of the roof 
of bil. sylvian fissures, sulcal effacement of the frontoparietal 
convexity, and abutment of the superior sagittal sinus. 
4. some tiny foci of high SI on T2WI in the bil. periventricular deep 
white matter, suggestive of leukoaraiosis.
5. abnormal high SI around the frontal and occipital horns of bil. lateral 
ventricles, r/o subcortical arteriosclerotic encephalopathy (SAE). 
6. prominent cisterna magna. 
7. multifocal stenosis at the M1 segment of right middle cerebral artery 
(MCA) and post-bifurcation M2 segment of left MCA; multifocal severe 
stenosis at the right vertebral artery (VA); fetal origin of the right 
posterior cerebral artery (PCA) from the right posterior communicating 
artery with absence of the P1 segment, and multifocal stenosis at the P2 
and P3 segments; segmental severe stenosis at the P3-4 segment of left 
PCA. 
8. no evidence of dural sinus thrombosis.
9. retention cyst, right maxillary antrum; left chronic otitis media. 

Impression :
subacute lacune, left cerebellum. 
cortical brain atrophy with leukoaraiosis and ventriculomegaly, r/o normal 
pressure hydrocephalus, r/o subcortical arteriosclerotic encephalopathy 
(SAE). 
prominent cisterna magna. 
multifocal stenosis, M1 segment of right MCA and post-bifurcation M2 
segment of left MCA; multifocal severe stenosis, right VA; right fetal PCA 
with multifocal stenosis, P2 and P3 segments; segmental severe stenosis, 
P3-4 segment of left PCA. 
retention cyst, right maxillary antrum; left chronic otitis media.

occipital scalp ecchymosis.

cortical brain atrophy with ventriculomegaly and leukoaraiosis. 
r/o recent lacunar infarcts, left corona radiata. 
old lacunar infarcts, left thalamus and basal ganglion. 
encephalomalacia, right MCA territory. 
no evidence of acute intracranial hemorrhage or skull fracture; bil. 
parietal scalp edema; left occipital scalp ecchymosis.

年    齡 : 56       醫囑醫師 : 吳鴻明
Brain with MRA +DWI without contrast
IMPRESSION I67.9 Cerebrovascular disease, unspecified,   照會資料 .,

Imaging findings :
MRI of the head (brain) without IV contrast enhancement shows:
1. acute lacunar and ischemic infarcts of abnormal bright SI on DWI and 
dark SI on ADC map at the right upper pons and midbrain, and right 
corpus callosum and occipital lobe.
2. cortical brain atrophy with prominent sulci and fissures, and 
ventriculomegaly.
3. some tiny foci of high SI on T2WI in the bil. periventricular deep 
white matter, suggestive of leukoaraiosis.
4. old lacunes or lacunar infarcts at the pons, and bil. thalami and 
basal ganglia. 
5. old insults with encephalomalacia at the bil. anterior frontal lobes 
and right posterior cerebral artery (PCA) territory. 
6. infundibular dilatation of the left posterior communicating artery 
(PComA) origin; multifocal stenosis at the pre- and post-bifurcation M1 
segments of right middle cerebral artery (MCA); multifocal severe 
stenosis at the right vertebral artery (VA) with segmental total 
occlusion of its intradural segment; fetal origin of the right posterior 
cerebral artery (PCA) from the right posterior communicating artery 
(PComA) with absence of the P1 segment, and total occlusion of its P2-4 
segment; segmental severe stenosis at the P3-4 segment of left PCA.  
7. no evidence of dural sinus thrombosis.
8. left chronic maxillary sinusitis; bil. chronic otitis media. 

Impression :
acute lacunar and ischemic infarcts, right upper pons and midbrain, and 
right corpus callosum and occipital lobe.
cortical brain atrophy with ventriculomegaly and leukoaraiosis. 
old lacunes or lacunar infarcts, pons, and bil. thalami and basal 
ganglia. 
encephalomalacia, bil. anterior frontal lobes and right PCA territory. 
infundibular dilatation, left PComA origin; multifocal stenosis, pre- and 
post-bifurcation M1 segments of right MCA; multifocal severe stenosis, 
right VA, with segmental total occlusion, intradural segment; right fetal 
PCA with total occlusion, P2-4 segment; segmental severe stenosis, P3-4 
segment of left PCA.  
left chronic maxillary sinusitis; bil. chronic otitis media. 

許昭禹醫師(放診專醫字第000430號)
